metrics_conclusion: In terms of chords and melody, Don't Cry For Me Argentina has complexity on par with the typical song, having near-average scores in Chord Complexity, Chord Progression Novelty and Chord-Bass Melody and below-average scores in Melodic Complexity and Chord-Melody Tension.

metadata.editComments: The main feauture of the first part of the verse is the tonic pedal. I don't think it is possible to have a G/C so I chose the nearest available note.
